An Uncommon Grace, on Hallmark Channel, (McGillis' 4th Amish themed film)[27]
Lead role in Mother of All Secrets in 2017 as Rose Lewis[28]
McGillis has been cast in the lead in the biographical film Annie Cook,[29] and also filmed Mother of All Secrets in early 2017 in Bermuda, and that trailer has already been released.[30][31]
McGillis married fellow Juilliard student Boyd Black in 1979, but the couple divorced in 1981.[32] She married Fred Tillman in 1989, and they have two daughters.[33] The couple divorced in 2002.
In 1982, McGillis was raped by two men in her New York apartment. The pair took turns to assault and stab her, as well as spit on her. Leroy Johnson, who was 15 years old at the time, was sentenced to three years in prison. The other man had all charges dropped through lack of corroborative evidence.[34]
McGillis came out as a lesbian in April 2009 during an interview with SheWired.[35][36] In 2010, McGillis entered into a civil union with Melanie Leis, a Philadelphia sales executive; she and McGillis met in 2000 when Leis was a bartender at Kelly's Caribbean Bar Grill & Brewery[37] in Key West, Florida,[38] which McGillis owned with her then-husband Fred Tillman.[39] They sold the restaurant in June 2017. Leis and McGillis broke up in 2011.[citation needed]
McGillis worked full-time with drug addicts and alcoholics at Seabrook House Drug Alcohol Rehab Center, a rehabilitation center in Bridgeton, New Jersey, when she and Leis shared a home in Collingswood.[40]
McGillis currently lives in Hendersonville, North Carolina. She teaches acting at The New York Studio for Stage and Screen NYS3 in Asheville, North Carolina.[41]
McGillis was left scratched and bruised after being reportedly assaulted by a woman who broke into her North Carolina home on June 17, 2016.[42] She said the attack, as well as others she has experienced in the past, led her to apply for a concealed carry gun permit to protect herself. Following the incident, a 38-year-old woman, Laurence Marie Dorn, was charged with second-degree burglary, misdemeanor larceny, misdemeanor stalking, assault and battery, and interfering with emergency communication.[42] Dorn was later convicted of misdemeanor breaking and entering.[43]

